{
  "document_id": "ps-2",
  "title": "Psalms 2",
  "type": "study-bible",
  "translation": "NJPS",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-2-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Why do nations assemble, and peoples plot vain things;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-2-1-commentary-1",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "Lit. “utter.”",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "ps",
        "chapter": 2,
        "verse": 1
      },
      "verse_start": 1,
      "verse_end": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-2-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "kings of the earth take their stand, and regents intrigue together against the Lord and against His anointed?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-2-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "“Let us break the cords of their yoke, shake off their ropes from us!”"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-2-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "He who is enthroned in heaven laughs; the Lord mocks at them."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-2-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "Then He speaks to them in anger, terrifying them in His rage,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-2-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "“But I have installed My king on Zion, My holy mountain!”"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-2-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "Let me tell of the decree: the Lord said to me, “You are My son, I have fathered you this day."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-2-7-commentary-2",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "Compare 2 Sam. 7.14, and Ps. 89.27 ff.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "ps",
        "chapter": 2,
        "verse": 7
      },
      "verse_start": 7,
      "verse_end": 7
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-2-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "Ask it of Me, and I will make the nations your domain; your estate, the limits of the earth."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-2-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "You can smash them with an iron mace, shatter them like potter’s ware.”"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-2-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "So now, O kings, be prudent; accept discipline, you rulers of the earth!"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-2-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "Serve the Lord in awe; tremble with fright,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-2-11-commentary-3",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "Meaning of Heb. uncertain; others “rejoice with trembling.”",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "ps",
        "chapter": 2,
        "verse": 11
      },
      "verse_start": 11,
      "verse_end": 11
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-2-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "pay homage in good faith, lest He be angered, and your way be doomed in the mere flash of His anger. Happy are all who take refuge in Him."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-2-12-commentary-4",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "Meaning of Heb. uncertain.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "ps",
        "chapter": 2,
        "verse": 12
      },
      "verse_start": 12,
      "verse_end": 12
    }
  ]
}